div.p:
"Lay up not for yourselves treasures upon earth, where moth and rust doth corrupt, and where
thieves break through and steal;

"But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust doth corrupt, and
where thieves do not break through nor steal;

"For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also"
(Matt. 6:19-21).

He cleansed the leper; 

        —turned water into wine; 

        —stilled the wind; 

        —calmed the waves; 

        —walked on the water; 

        —healed the sick and the halt; 

        —cast out evil spirits; 

        —returned sight to the blind; 

        —restored life to the dead.
